extraction_issues.issue: DO (Dissolved Oxygen) reported as 'ND* (S1–S8)' for all secondary drain sites in both seasons. No detection limit provided. All secondary drains have DO below detection.
Lead (Pb) reported as 'ND* (S1–S8)' for all secondary drain sites during pre-monsoon season. No detection limit provided.
Minimum Cr reported as 'ND* (S2,S5,S7)' during pre-monsoon - multiple sites below detection, cannot extract numeric minimum.
Minimum Cr reported as 'ND* (S2,S3,S4,S7)' during post-monsoon - multiple sites below detection, cannot extract numeric minimum.
Minimum Pb reported as 'ND* (S3,S4,S5,S8)' during post-monsoon - multiple sites below detection, cannot extract numeric minimum.
Minimum Cd reported as 'ND* (S1–S5,S7,S8)' during post-monsoon - most sites below detection, cannot extract numeric minimum.

Data for intermediate Najafgarh drain sites (N2-N14) and Yamuna River sites (Y1-Y2) are only presented in bar charts/figures and cannot be accurately extracted without digitization. Only visual trends can be interpreted.
Heavy metal concentration ranges mentioned as being in supplementary tables S1 and S2 are not included in the provided document pages.
Detection limits for parameters reported as 'ND*' (not detected) are not provided in the paper. Asterisk note only states 'ND refers to not detected'.
Table 4 presents min/max ranges across all 8 secondary drains with site identifiers in parentheses. Individual site values cannot be extracted for sites not at min or max positions.
